  "response": "Here are several strategies to help get rid of persistent pimples:\n\n1. Skincare routine\n- Cleanse face twice daily\n- Use salicylic acid or benzoyl peroxide treatments\n- Exfoliate regularly\n- Use non-comedogenic moisturizer\n\n2. Over-the-counter treatments\n- Spot treatments with benzoyl peroxide\n- Hydrocolloid acne patches\n- Tea tree oil\n- Retinol creams\n\n3. Lifestyle changes\n- Stay hydrated\n- Eat a balanced diet\n- Reduce sugar and dairy intake\n- Get enough sleep\n- Manage stress\n- Change pillowcases frequently\n\n4. Professional treatments\n- Consult a dermatologist\n- Chemical peels\n- Prescription medications like antibiotics\n- Topical retinoids\n- Isotretinoin for severe cases\n\n5. Avoid\n- Touching or picking at pimples\n- Heavy makeup\n- Harsh scrubbing\n- Excessive sun exposure\n\n6. Natural remedies\n- Aloe vera\n- Green tea extract\n- Honey masks\n- Zinc supplements\n\nIf pimples persist or worsen despite these methods, consult a dermatologist for personalized treatment.",
